Le drupalcamp est proposé par l'association Drupal France et francophonie. Il s'est déroulé sur 3 jours, du 27 au 29 octobre 2017, à Lannion (22).

The biggest European Drupal event reimagined.

Drupal Europe (10-14 September 2018) is both a technology conference and a family reunion for the Drupal community. It brings together 1600+ attendees with shared interests in great digital experiences and solving challenges together.

The conference puts an emphasis on contribution with opportunities throughout the whole week and especially on Monday and Friday.

Ten industry tracks focus on real life case studies and success stories alongside emerging new best practices. Workshops throughout the week provide hands-on opportunities to broaden your knowledge.

Drupal Europe is put on by a group of community volunteers in collaboration with the German Drupal Association and the Drupal Europe Foundation.

Le « Drupalcamp », le cycle de conférences itinérant de l'association Drupal France & Francophonie, retourne en 2019 à Paris 3ème les 15, 16 et 17 février.

Depuis sa création, l'association est passée par de nombreuses villes tels que Nantes, Toulouse, Montpellier, Lannion, Lyon. A chaque étape, l'événement dédie sa programmation à une thématique particulière. Cette année, l'accent fera une part belle aux retours d'expériences, aux conférences techniques et à la découverte.

De nombreux speakers talentueux ont répondu à l'appel et viendront partager leur savoir sur une des thématiques avec vos auditeurs.

Chaque cœur de métier sera mise en avant lors d'une présentation sous la forme d'un retour d'expérience client [2] que vous pouvez découvrir et échanger.

Behind the Stream - How A11yTalks Creates Accessible Virtual Events with the A11yTalks team.

Have you ever wondered how the A11yTalks team, month after month, delivers accessible online events? Our team is excited to let you see behind the scenes how we prepare, perform, and produce high-quality and meaningful conversations around digital accessibility.

In this interactive panel discussion, you will hear from members of the A11yTalks team on what it takes to deliver content to a wide audience where everyone can participate in the discussion. From event preparation tips to selecting and setting up our speakers for success, you’ll walk away with ideas you can immediately use at your next virtual event. We'll share our event preparation checklist and discuss actions anyone can take to prepare for your next accessible event. The A11yTalks team would also like to hear from you, the viewer, on how we can improve as we head into 2024 and beyond.

Mark your calendar: November 28th, 12PM (ET)

DrupalCamp Essen 2010

Drupal Developer Days 2010 will be held on the campus Lothstr. of the Munich University of Applied Sciences from May 7 (pre-registration) until May 9 2010. Munich University of Applied Sciences is the official co-sponsor of our event and has made sure that the walls are painted in a very nice drupalish blue! (not true).

Central location, connected and top modern: We are looking forward to welcoming you to the Campus Lothstraße of the Hochschule München from the 8th to 9th May 2010. The very modern location of our Co-Organizer offers all your conference needs.

What you can expect from us are: technical up-to-date conference rooms for sessions and discussions, seminar rooms for Ad-Hoc-sessions, code-sprints and practical workshops as well as a welcoming foyer in a typical Drupal blue for the social part of the event.

Wir laden Euch ein, am 12. März 2011 gemeinsam mit uns einen Tag rund um Drupal zu gestalten.

Das Institut für Informatik der Universität Rostock wird uns beherbergen. Ab 9 Uhr ist Einlass, die Veranstaltung wird 10 Uhr beginnen. Nach dem eigentlichen Drupal Day steht uns der Klub "Klock 8" für ausgiebiges Socializing zur Verfügung.

Die Registrierung für die Teilnahme am Drupal Day ist auf der Website http://www.drupal-mv.de/ möglich, der Kartenverkauf läuft im Shop des Drupal-Initiative e.V..

Wir sehen uns in Rostock! :)
DrupalCamping 2011

Das Europäische Drupal Netzwerk veranstaltet am 25. und 26. Juni 2011 in Berlin das Drupal Design Camp Berlin 2011, und möchte euch dazu herzlichst einladen.

Das Drupal Design Camp entstand als Ergebnis eines Treffens von führenden Drupal Entwicklern und Designern die sich im Rahmen der DrupalCon Kopenhagen getroffen hatten und beschlossen haben europaweite Design Camps zu organisieren.

Das erste Drupal Design Camp in Prag im letzten Herbst hat durch seinen Erfolg die Nachfrage nach speziell auf Frontententwickler ausgerichteten Events bestätigt und wir möchten diese Nachfrage gerne mit dem diesjährigen Drupal Design Camp Berlin weiter befriedigen und die wachsende Basis der Designer für Drupal ausbauen und Interessierte mit den notwendigen Techniken und Workflows vertraut machen.

Der Fokus unseres Camps liegt im Gegensatz zu regulären Drupal Camps vor allem auf Design, UX (User Experience) und Theming für Drupal.

Dazu haben wir eine Auswahl von hochkarätigen Rednern gewinnen können, unter anderem Jeff Burnz, den Initiator der Drupal 8 Design Initiative.

Weitere Informationen findet ihr unter

http://www.facebook.com/DrupalDesignCamp
http://drupaldesigncamp.net

Das Camp wird auf englisch gehalten, Tickets kosten 20€ (normal) und 50€ (community-sponsoring).

For this month's Meeting, Liam McDermott will share his experiences with integrating AI into the development workflow. This will include an overview of several tools and models and their benefits and limitations.

Topics include:

  • Case study of migrating a Joomla extension to Drupal 10 using ChatGPT 4
  • Daily use of Github Copilot while coding
  • Running an LLM (Large Language Model) locally to get ChatGPT-like results

We will conclude with a discussion of what the future may hold for this new field.

list.title: November Meetup: Integrating AI into the development workflow

Welcome to DrupalCon Munich 2012

DrupalCon is an international event that brings together the people who use, develop, design, and support the Drupal platform. More than just another trade show or industry conference, it’s a shared experience that seeks to inspire and engage. DrupalCon Munich will feature dozens of curated sessions and panels from some of the most influential people and brightest minds within the Drupal community and beyond, as well as countless opportunities for networking, code sprints, informal conversations, and more. Whether you’re new to the community, have been around a while, or are just curious to see what all the fuss is about - we have a place for you.

This year the Drupal Developer Days will start monday april 13th, 2015 and stop on sunday april 19th, 2015. In order to contribute in the most efficient way to Drupal 8.

The sprints are the key moment of the conference, during a whole week, contributors from all over the world are going to stay in the same room to help Drupal move forward. During those days you connect with the heart of the open source and can feel the pulse of true collaboration. There is always a before and an after your first sprint. Everyone is welcome, new comers and old timers. The topics are really broad, you can sprint on Drupal 8 core, porting your contributed module, improving Drupal.org, working on the frontend team, on the Drupal infrastructure and every topic that you care about!

The week basically ends with 3 days of sessions. The content of the sessions covers various topics, you can hear / speak about headless Drupal, responsive design, NoSQL storage, continous delivery, Scrum, Composer, working with Sass, etc. Find out more on our dedicated page to the sessions.
